      "id": "bug-011",
      "timestamp": "2026-07-01T09:20:00.000Z",
      "error_message": "tsc exited immediately with TS5101 (baseUrl deprecated), so `tsc --noEmit` has never actually type-checked this project's files — it always failed before reaching them.",
      "file": "quran-hifz-mobile/tsconfig.json",
      "root_cause": "tsconfig.json (unchanged since initial commit) sets \"baseUrl\": \".\" without \"ignoreDeprecations\": \"6.0\", and the pinned typescript@6.0.3 treats baseUrl as a hard deprecation error, aborting before checking any file.",
      "fix": "Added \"ignoreDeprecations\": \"6.0\" to compilerOptions so tsc actually runs. This uncovered ~12 pre-existing files with real type errors that predate this session: missing theme colors (theme.cream, theme.greenPale referenced but not defined in lib/theme.ts), Badge/StatBox components used with props (children, pct) their Props types don't declare, `number && {...}` conditional style spreads (e.g. `0 && {...}`) that don't satisfy RN's style types, a StyleSheet.absoluteFillObject typo (should be absoluteFill), and a StatusBar backgroundColor prop that doesn't exist on its type. None of these are in files touched this session (app/(portal)/admin/special_tracks.tsx, app/(portal)/parent/{attendance,dashboard,homework_view,messages,recordings,timeline}.tsx, app/(portal)/student/{points,store}.tsx, app/(portal)/teacher/{evaluate,grouphomework,recordlesson}.tsx) except app/_layout.tsx and app/index.tsx which inherited the absoluteFillObject/StatusBar/global.css issues verbatim from the pre-existing code they were built from.",
      "tags": [
        "auto-detected",
        "type-fix",
        "tsconfig",
        "systemic",
        "mobile"
